==== More ranks ====

* '''Sergeant''' - A pillar of the community and a role model for other officers. They are the on scene supervisor when a higher ranking officer is not on scene.
* '''Corporal''' - A member who has gone out of their way to uphold the LPD community values, and can show new members the right ways to pursue a fruitful and fun experience.
* '''Senior Officer''' - A member who has attended Senior Officer training and has proven themselves a capable leader and has good knowledge of the LPD.
* '''Officer''' - A proven member of the LPD community, they are active in VRChat and on the Discord. They are a vast majority of members, and are members that casually enjoy LPD content.
* '''Recruit''' - Freshly trained members that are just ready to experience the full journey that is the LPD.
* '''Cadet''' - Recently accepted members in the LPD, they still need to get training before they can go on patrol, or participate in LPD-only events.

== Event Hosts ==
Today, the LPD carries out an assortment of On Duty Events for the community to partake under the command of several Event Hosts. These events are either Patrol Events, Most Wanted, Search Warrants, and many other special events. These special events are either collaborations with other communities, (Such as the SCP x LPD Collab done in May of 2021), Or special events hosted for the community, such as a 24 Hour Patrol for the yearly anniversary of the group held on November 18th, and the 24 hour patrol event for New Years Eve.

They also host Off Duty Events for the community to go and meet the members of the LPD. These events can range from Movie Nights, LPD Community Lazerdome, World Hopping, Game Nights, Anime Nights, and many more.

== Teams ==
There are various teams within the LPD, many of these help keep the community thriving and active. Members may apply to a ''majority'' of these teams to help contribute to the community if they so wish. Select teams may require a higher rank, or specific knowledge in a field to join. 

=== Recruiter Team ===
Members of the community responsible for managing the application process. Applications are done daily, leaving about a week to two weeks ahead in the process. 

=== Trainer Team ===
Trainers are members that help train new Cadets to familiarize them with the core values of the LPD, along with preparing them on their journey in the department. Later in their career, Officers may partake in a Senior Officer training organized and hosted by certified members of this team to elevate to the rank of Senior Officer. 

=== Mentor Team ===
The Mentor Team is responsible for being alongside new Recruits. They help Recruits integrate into the department, and provides advice to propel them as they get their start. 

=== Event Hosting Team ===
Event hosts are members in the community responsible for hosting various events, such as patrol events, or special events for the community. These members are charismatic, energetic, and help keep the community thriving. 

=== Development Team ===
Developers are members of the community responsible for creating various assets for the LPD, such as worlds, and avatars. They help keep these assets up to date, along with making sure they meet acceptable standards for the community. 

=== Avatar Approval Team ===
The Approval Team is responsible for approving custom LPD models, such as patrol models, SLRT operators, and more. Approvers are responsible for upholding the stylistic guidelines of LPD avatars to the general community for those who wish to create a custom model. 

=== LMT Trainer Team ===
LMT Trainers are members within the community specialized in familiarizing Officers in the roleplay of Local Medical Technicians, (LMTs). These members help Officers better understand how to play the role, and acquaint them with the style of roleplay the subdivision portrays. 

=== SLRT Trainer Team ===
SLRT Trainers, much like LMT Trainers, are members within the community specialized in familiarizing Senior Officers in the roleplay of the Special Local Response Team, (SLRT). These members help Senior Officers better understand how to play the role, and acquaint them with the style of roleplay the subdivision portrays. 

=== Corrections Officer Trainer Team ===
CO Trainers, much like LMT & SLRT Trainers, are members within the community specialized in familiarizing Corporals in the roleplay of the Corrections division. Correction Officers are responsible for maintaining a prison during patrol events, and are usually the rank of Corporal. New Officers may help assist existing Correction Officers in maintaining this prison if they desire without training. 

=== Instigator Team ===
This team comprises of LPD Officers that take on the role of being an Instigator. Instigators are responsible for creating wacky, and adrenaline filled scenarios to not only impress the public, but also provide a fun experience to Officers on patrol. Instigators also organize in-house 911 calls at any time to allow Officers to participate, and resolve the problem. 

=== Media Production Team ===
The Media Team is responsible for creating social media content for the LPD, along with advertising and media asset creation. These members have a great taste in creativity, along with know-how in various media production fields. 

=== Chat Moderation Team ===
Chat Moderators are members in the community responsible for moderating the LPD Discord, and making sure the server remains family-friendly. 

=== Programming Team ===
The Programming Team is responsible for helping keep the core systems and bots that drive various functions and logistics to keep the LPD and it's teams afloat.

== Legacy ==
Although the LPD was initially founded to protect Lolis against lewders, it quickly developed into a full-fledged VRChat police force. Today, the LPD is promoting a self-image of comedic interaction under the guise of "protecting the security of VRChat." This group is mainly operating for entertainment. Though, if the need arises, LPD officers are known to help users.

The LPD hosts a variety of different events for the community. They can range fromcarrying out various sting operations to civic services and community service, especially for people who are new to VRChat, or simply patrolling around the VRChat community and interacting with the public. In January of 2021, they began a short series on their YouTube channel, called LPD Files. '''Khangaluwu''' is in charge of filming the series. The first episode was released on February 14, but after a few months it was taken down due to Copyrighted music. In May of the same year, they re-released it with a whole custom soundtrack.

=== Social media content ===
The LPD has two social media pages. On their '''[https://twitter.com/LPD_vr Twitter profile]''' you will find up to date information and entertaining pictures and videos made by the Social Media Team, and their '''[https://www.youtube.com/@LPD_vr YouTube Channel]''' was recently revived with new content. The team works under the leadership of Arkanium, and Sukadia. 

The group historically produced an '''[https://youtu.be/ff4vf2FGzI0 online comedy-documentary]''' called '''LPD: VRChat Stories''', and frequently adds more entertainment on YouTube and Twitter. 

They also created a new short Documentary Series for the group called "LPD Files." Currently, the Media Production team works on short, satirical clips dubbed '''"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pid-EBNRRvg&list=PLF2k3zhFfXLbg7XLqtEtFs9n-dTYZQS9l Instructional Tapes]"''', which put a spin on both common occurrences & jokes within the community, along with highlighting the actions of it's protagonist 'Becky'. 

=== LPD Files ===
[[File:LPDFilesPoster1-7.webp|right|frameless|255x255px]]
After the nuke, '''Khangaluwu''' began work on the new series for the LPD, called LPD Files.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bUC3Pp-uU5w LPD Files - Episode 1: Love Hurts] at YouTube.com</ref><ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jENSvrFK9Kg LPD Files - Episode 2: Love Makes War] at YouTube.com.</ref> 

This follows the story of a new recruit, named Marney, and their adventures through the metaverse of VRChat and explore the story of the Love Gang, the main antagonist of the story. As of October 2021, they have released two episodes so far, with a 3rd episode in the works. 

Unfortunately, due to real life circumstances, Khangaluwu stepped down to the rank of Adviser on January 29th, but then retired fully shortly after.

Since then, no new info has came out about Episode 3, and the future of LPD Files.

